<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../partials/head', {title:hosting_data.title, description:hosting_data.description}) %>
</head>
<body>

<div class="content hosting subpage-content">
  <%- include('../partials/header', {title:hosting_data.title, subheading: 'Hosting Options'}) %>
    <div>
    <h3>
      - <a id="shivernet">Shivernet Hosting</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      You can host your Shiver Dock personal site on <a href="https://shivernet.social">shivernet.social</a>, a service provided by <a href="https://bluesharkfriends.com">Blue Shark Friends</a>. Shiver Dock <a href="https://bluesharkfriends.com/kickstarter">Kickstarter</a> backers who pledge at any website reward tier receive a free year of hosting, but future years will require an annual subscription.
    </p>
    <div class="pros-cons">
      <div class="column pros">
        <h4>Pros</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Supported by Blue Shark Friends</li>
          <li>Affordable</li>
          <li>Option to join beta testing</li>
          <li>Guaranteed interoperability with other Shiver-powered sites</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="column cons">
        <h4>Cons</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>New software</li>
          <li>Small company with limited capacity</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>
      - <a id="dynamic">Self-Funded Dynamic Hosting</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      You can pay for your own hosting and serve the Shiver Dock personal site pages dynamically. This is the recommended route for those who can afford their own hosting as any future upgrades that we make available should be compatible. Need help with setup? <a href="https://cal.com/bluesharkfriends">Schedule a consultation</a> with Blue Shark Friends. We will include instructions for running the Node app in the package.
    </p>
    <div class="pros-cons">
      <div class="column pros">
        <h4>Pros</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Independent of Blue Shark Friends</li>
          <li>User-friendly options available
            <ul>
              <li>e.g. Heroku</li>
              <li>other Node.js hosting services</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Likely to support future features</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="column cons">
        <h4>Cons</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Most expensive</li>
          <li>Requires technical expertise</li>
          <li>Research required to ensure host supports Node.js</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>
      - <a id="static">Static Hosting</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      You can render your Shiver Dock personal site as static pages that can be hosted anywhere that offers hosting for static sites. Personal sites generated by Shiver Dock currently contain no dynamic elements, but in the future dynamic elements will be offered.
    </p>
    <div class="pros-cons">
      <div class="column pros">
        <h4>Pros</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Multiple free static hosting platforms available
            <ul>
              <li>GitHub Pages</li>
              <li>Neocities</li>
              <li>Surge.sh</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Quick setup</li>
          <li>Setup documentation available</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="column cons">
        <h4>Cons</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Not compatible with future updates<br />
            <small style="font-size:x-small">Future updates will have dynamic features</small>
          </li>
          <li>Not recommended long-term for digital community growth but works in a pinch</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>
      - <a id="diy">List Existing Site</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      You can list an existing site on the Shivernet, and forgo using Shiver Dock.
    </p>
    <div class="pros-cons">
      <div class="column pros">
        <h4>Pros</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Use what you already have</li>
          <li>Wide variety of options<br />
            <small style="font-size:x-small">If you can link it, we can list it!</small>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="column cons">
        <h4>Cons</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Future community interoperability at risk</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br />
</div>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>

<div class="poweredby">
  <div class="cardlink">
    <a href="https://bluesharkfriends.com/solutions"><span class="linkspan"></span></a>
    <div class="fitcontent"><p><small class="bytext">powered by</small><br /><em>Shiver</em><br /><small class="subtext">A website creation framework</small></p></div>
  </div>
</div>
  
</body>
</html>